cal galaxies\nand the cD galaxy NGC 3311. We conclude that our current results cannot\ndiscriminate between the bulge/halo scenario. Although there is a hint that the\nred GC velocity dispersion might correlate better with M_BH than the blue GC\nvelocity dispersion, the number statistics are still too low to be certain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Apr 2013 20:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
